article.headline: Northeastern 73, New Hampshire 67
article.story: DURHAM, N.H. (AP) -- Jose Juan Barea scored 36 points, including his team's final 11, to lead Northeastern to a 73-67 victory Wednesday night over New Hampshire. Barea started his 11-point run with a three-pointer hat gave NU (13-7 overall, 9-2 America East) its first lead of the second half (65-63) with 2:26 to go. He then buried two three-pointers capped b y a pair of free throws for the victory with 21 seconds remaining. UNH (7-13 overall, 3-8 America East) missed two three-point attempts in the final 16 seconds. UNH led most of the game and was up by as many as 11 points (55-44). But NU then went on a 13-4 run that cut the Wildcat lead to two points (59-57) on a three-pointer by Marcus Barnes with 5:27 to play. UNH was led in scoring by Craig Walls, who poured in a season-high 20 points and grabbed six rebounds. Ben Sturgill finished with 17 points and forward Mike Christensen added 13. Barea was the only Husky to score in double figures. Barnes was the next-highest with nine points, while Bobby Kelly chipped in eight.
